                "config_description": "Created from Cloud Cost, Snowflake MT Cost version #247\n\nThis transformation put together infrastructure cost for AWS, Azure, GCP, BigQuery and Multitenant (=Keboola) Snowflake. Reseller Snowflake is then worked in the next transformation that assigned the cost to specific companies (as for reseller it is only about matching with the specific customer - one contract - one customer).\nKBDB is currently not split as we have no easy way to map it.\n\nUpdated – removed some conditions, simplifying the stack definition until we determine the correct mapping from the SRE team. Also, BYODB is included in the customer group. Fix with aggregated values, when incremental load was removing rows because our PK wasnt too unique.Added snowflake resell- not used precalculated reseller data as it seems not to be correct, Created list of kbdb and resell (bud under our org) companies- this needs to be automated (maybe we can somehow catch account name from queries history and then used this account name to find correct records in snowflake usage, or maybe it can be added to salesforce). Added BQ/GCP history.  for now, all dedicated account (snfk/bq)  and single tenants has assigned also company id so it can be linked to their consumption or arr.",
