                "config_id": "01kj52g9k6xkv9r0c6htg6asd1",
                "config_name": "01 FI COA Preparation (Xero KDS)",
                "config_description": "## 01 FI COA Preparation (Xero KDS)\n\nBuild COA hierarchy with account type mapping and recursive rollup. Reads ERP account table + DIM_BUSINESS_SUBUNIT -> produces DIM_COA (L1 Dim) + COA_DEBUG_COUNT_CHECK (Validation). MAP_ACCOUNT_TYPE and MAP_FININ_STRUCTURE are inlined as VALUES CTEs in the SQL.\n\n### Data Lineage\n\n```\n  ├── Account               (external)\n  └── DIM_BUSINESS_SUBUNIT  (l1-dim)\n  │\n  ▼\n  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  │  01 FI COA Preparation (Xero KDS)  :  coa-enrichment-and-hierarchy  │\n  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  │\n  ▼\n  ├──► DIM_COA                (l1-dim)\n  └──► COA_DEBUG_COUNT_CHECK  (validation)\n```\n\n### Inputs\n\n| Source | Alias | Bucket | Note |\n|--------|-------|--------|------|\n| `<erp_account_table>` | Account | -- | SE must configure -- source depends on ERP extractor |\n| `out.c-fi-l1-dim.DIM_BUSINESS_SUBUNIT` | DIM_BUSINESS_SUBUNIT | out.c-fi-l1-dim |  |\n\n### Outputs\n\n| Source | Destination | Bucket |\n|--------|-------------|--------|\n| DIM_COA | `out.c-fi-l1-dim.DIM_COA` | out.c-fi-l1-dim |\n| COA_DEBUG_COUNT_CHECK | `out.c-fi-validation.COA_DEBUG_COUNT_CHECK` | out.c-fi-validation |\n\n### Blocks\n\n1. **coa-enrichment-and-hierarchy** -- Map account types via MAP_ACCOUNT_TYPE JOIN, build recursive hierarchy, flag leaf nodes\n   - SQL: 01-dc-coa-enriched, 02-dim-coa\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Type | Name | Value | Purpose |\n|------|------|-------|---------|\n| variable | `finin_assets` | `--` | Root node for Assets |\n| variable | `finin_liabilities` | `--` | Root node for Liabilities |\n| variable | `finin_revenue` | `--` | Root node for Revenue |\n| variable | `finin_expenses` | `--` | Root node for Expenses |\n| variable | `finin_equity` | `--` | Root node for Equity |",
                "component_id": "keboola.snowflake-transformation",
                "component_name": "Snowflake SQL"
