                "config_name": "02 FI Journal Entries (Xero KDS)",
                "config_description": "## 02 FI Journal Entries (Xero KDS)\n\nCreate FT_FIN_JOURNAL from ERP General Ledger data. Maps GL transactions to FI journal schema with sign convention, entity scoping, and period assignment. Customer-specific -- SE must customize SQL per ERP source.\n\n### Data Lineage\n\n```\n  ├── GLEntries             (external)\n  ├── DIM_COA               (l1-dim)\n  └── DIM_BUSINESS_SUBUNIT  (l1-dim)\n  │\n  ▼\n  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  │  02 FI Journal Entries (Xero KDS)  :  journal-preparation  │\n  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  │\n  ▼\n  ├──► STG_JOURNAL_ENRICHED  (intermediate)\n  └──► FT_FIN_JOURNAL        (l1-fact)\n```\n\n### Inputs\n\n| Source | Alias | Bucket | Note |\n|--------|-------|--------|------|\n| `<erp_gl_table>` | GLEntries | -- | SE must configure -- source depends on ERP extractor |\n| `out.c-fi-l1-dim.DIM_COA` | DIM_COA | out.c-fi-l1-dim |  |\n| `out.c-fi-l1-dim.DIM_BUSINESS_SUBUNIT` | DIM_BUSINESS_SUBUNIT | out.c-fi-l1-dim |  |\n\n### Outputs\n\n| Source | Destination | Bucket |\n|--------|-------------|--------|\n| STG_JOURNAL_ENRICHED | `out.c-fi-intermediate.STG_JOURNAL_ENRICHED` | out.c-fi-intermediate |\n| FT_FIN_JOURNAL | `out.c-fi-l1-fact.FT_FIN_JOURNAL` | out.c-fi-l1-fact |\n\n### Blocks\n\n1. **journal-preparation** -- Enrich GL entries with master data into STG_JOURNAL_ENRICHED, then produce final FT_FIN_JOURNAL with sign convention and opening balances\n   - SQL: 01-stg-journal-enriched, 02-ft-fin-journal\n\n### Deployment Note\n\n> This transformation ships as a skeleton (WHERE 1=0). SE must uncomment and adjust the INSERT logic to match their ERP GL extractor output. See commented example in SQL template.",
