                "config_name": "Salesforce - Lead/Contact Score",
                "config_description": "This transformation processes lead and contact data from Salesforce, along with event and campaign data, to calculate scores based on various criteria such as event participation, email engagement, job title, and other attributes. It filters out irrelevant or deleted records, calculates cumulative scores, and identifies leads and contacts that meet specific thresholds, marking them as Marketing Qualified Leads (MQLs). The transformation also maps events to different stages of the lead lifecycle, ensuring progression from awareness to decision-making stages.\n\nThe output tables contain updated scores and stages for leads and contacts, reflecting changes based on recent interactions and attributes. This allows for more accurate tracking and management of lead and contact engagement, facilitating targeted marketing and sales efforts.",
